{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/init(font:textColor:textView:delegate:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/gutterWidth","doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/isFlipped"]},{"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView\/draw(_:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GutterView","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the gutter needs more space (when the number of digits in the numbers increases eg. adding a line after line 99),"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it will notify it’s delegate via the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterViewDelegate\/gutterViewWidthDidUpdate(newWidth:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method. In"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CodeEditSourceEditor"},{"type":"text","text":", this notifies the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/TextViewController","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", which in turn updates the textview’s edge insets"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to adjust for the new leading inset."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This view also listens for selection updates, and draws a selected background on selected lines to keep the illusion"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that the gutter’s line numbers are inline with the line itself.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The gutter view has insets of it’s own that are relative to the widest line index. By default, these insets are 20px"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"leading, and 12px trailing. However, this view also has a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GutterView\/backgroundEdgeInsets"},{"type":"text","text":" property, that pads"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the rect that has a background drawn. This allows the text to be scrolled under the gutter view for 8px before being"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"overlapped by the gutter. It should help the textview keep the cursor visible if the user types while the cursor is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"off the leading edge of the editor.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"The gutter view displays line numbers that match the text view’s line indexes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This view is used as a scroll view’s ruler view. It sits on top of the text view so text scrolls underneath the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"gutter if line wrapping is disabled.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"c:@M@CodeEditSourceEditor@objc(cs)GutterView","title":"GutterView","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GutterView"}],"modules":[{"name":"CodeEditSourceEditor"}],"roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GutterView","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/CodeEditSource